Northcliff residents on high alert for a baboon on the loose in the Johannesburg suburb. JOHANNESBURG - As the much-awaited release of the live-action remake of the Lion King draws nearer, a real-life Rafiki may be searching for a pride rock of its own. The baboon has been spotted running from roof to roof at Northcliff Corner.  Animal welfare group Claw is on the chase, trying to capture the primate. READ: Baboon on the loose in Northcliff “The baboon was first spotted in Florida and it is now in Northcliff. CLAW is on the way to capture please bring your dogs and cats inside if you live in the area,” said Johan Veldman from SCP security. Residents are urged to be safe and not to approach the animal.